---

# SclJet multi-page table writer

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
def mkRows(n: Int, i: Int, acc: List[List[SqliteValue]]): List[List[SqliteValue]] =
  if i > n then acc.reverse
  else mkRows(n, i + 1, List(SqlInteger(i.toLong), SqlText("value" + i.toString)) :: acc)

// 45 rows overflow a single 512-byte leaf, so page 2 becomes a table-interior
// root over the leaf pages — a multi-level B-tree the reader/integrity_check accept.
buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(n INTEGER, v TEXT)", mkRows(45, 1, Nil)) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
